The paper proposes a new method for few-shot learning using infinite mixture prototypes. This involves clustering data into sets of clusters, which is a common technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with image classification, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of adaptive capacity, which is a key aspect of artificial intelligence, suggesting that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses clustering, which is a common technique in natural language processing, suggesting that it could belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses neural networks, which is a common technique in neural engineering, suggesting that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
